title: Mudall, New South Wales
text:
Mudall Parish (Oxley County), New South Wales is a <a href="rural%20locality">rural locality</a> of <a href="Bogan%20Shire">Bogan Shire</a> and a <a href="Lands%20administrative%20divisions%20of%20Australia">civil parish</a> of <a href="Oxley%20County%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Oxley County, New South Wales</a>, a <a href="Cadastral%20divisions%20of%20New%20South%20Wales">Cadastral divisions of New South Wales</a>.
The <a href="civil%20parish">parish</a> is on the <a href="Bogan%20River">Bogan River</a> <a href="south">south</a> of <a href="Nyngan">Nyngan</a>.
The topography is flat with a <a href="K%C3%B6ppen%20climate%20classification">Köppen climate classification</a> of BsK (Hot semi arid).
The economy in the parish is based on broad acre <a href="agriculture">agriculture</a>, based on <a href="Wheat">Wheat</a>, <a href="sheep">sheep</a> and <a href="cattle">cattle</a>.
The traditional owners of the area are the <a href="Wiradjuri">Wiradjuri</a> people.
